{
  "answer": "**Chapter 50** of *Diwan-E-Ghalib* is titled **\"Gham khaane mein boda dil-e-nakaam bahut hai\"**, which is the *matlaʿ* (opening couplet) of the ghazal.[^1]\n\nThe *matlaʿ* reads:\n\n**Original (Urdu):**  \nغم کھانے میں بودا دل_ناکام بہت ہے  \nیہ رنج کہ کم ہے مئے_گلفام بہت ہے[^2]\n\n**Transliteration:**  \nGham khaane mein boda dil-e-nakaam bahut hai  \nYeh ranj ke kam hai mai-e-gulfaam bahut hai[^3]\n\n**Translation:**  \nThis weak, failed heart's capacity for pain is more than enough;  \nThe grief that rose-red wine is on the wane is more than enough.[^4]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [chapter](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/50-gham-khaane-mein-boda-dil-e-nakaam-bahut-hai/translation/).\n\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/50-gham-khaane-mein-boda-dil-e-nakaam-bahut-hai/original/#p-a0be2a).\n\n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/50-gham-khaane-mein-boda-dil-e-nakaam-bahut-hai/transliteration/#p-d3a1ee).\n\n[^4]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/50-gham-khaane-mein-boda-dil-e-nakaam-bahut-hai/translation/#p-b39b6a).",
